values.name: Active
values.doc: Replication link is active.

values.name: Catchup
values.doc: Replica is catching-up with the primary. This can occur after the replica is created or after a promotion is triggered.

values.name: Provisioning
values.doc: Replica and replication link to the primary is being created.

values.name: Updating
values.doc: Replication link is being updated due to a change on the replica or an upgrade.

values.name: Broken

values.name: Reconfiguring
values.doc: Replication link is re-configuring due to a promotion event.

values.doc: Name is invalid.

values.doc: Name already exists.

enums.name: MongoClusterPromoteOption

values.name: Forced
values.doc: Promote option forces the promotion without waiting for the replica to be caught up to the primary. This can result in data-loss so should only be used during disaster recovery scenarios.

values.name: Switchover
values.doc: Promotion will switch the current replica cluster to the primary role and the original primary will be switched to a replica role, maintaining the replication link.
